  "body": "in networks with high latency, these types of disconnects are common, even with otherwise \"good\" peers. If even the best peers are laggy, it doesn't make sense to continually disconnect for these reasons:\r\n\r\nFor 3 types of infractions, don't actively disconnect if we are still finding peers\r\n* timeout\r\n* useless response\r\n* IO exception (common from DeFramer)\r\n",
